            <h2 id="sb04">Frontier Justice</h2>
            <br>

            <h4 id="louis"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "06006" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                              data-index="06006">Louis
                    Pasteur</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Louis makes the skill check, not the player, so Doyle's Hoyle can be used. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=113597#p1467534">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="jail"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "06011" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                             data-index="06011">Gomorra
                    Jail</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Shootouts take place during the High Noon phase.
            </ul>

            <h4 id="diable"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "06012" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                               data-index="06012">Diable en
                    Boite</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>As it is a React ability (not Resolution), if it causes one posse to become empty, it will not
                    immediately stop the shootout, and so the other player will still have to take casualties (if
                    applicable). (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=113784#p1471110">Source</a>)
                <li>If the equipped dude is saved with Arnold McCadish or Lay On Hands, you cannot activate the React
                    ability. (<a href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=113960#p1473630">Source</a>)
                <li>Once you assign casualties to a dude, removing him from the shootout will not prevent you from
                    having to resolve these casualties. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&amp;t=115275"
                            target="_blank">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="rmm"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "06014" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                            data-index="06014">Recursive
                    Motion Machine</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>If a card effect says "move this dude into a posse", but the dude doesn't actually change location,
                    you cannot use the React ability. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=113784#p1471110">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="fancyhat"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "06016" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                 data-index="06016">Fancy
                    New Hat</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Any pre-existing influence-reducing effects are ignored as long as the Hat is worn.
                <li>Any subsequent influence-reducing effects are prevented as long as the Hat is worn.
                <li>Does not protect from traits (Hustings) or your own effects (Mortimer Parsons) (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=113730#p1469940">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="shield"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "06018" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                               data-index="06018">Shield of
                    Faith</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Your casualties are reduced by 1 only for this round; the rest of the effect applies for the whole
                    shootout.
                <li>Protects from Takin' Ya With Me and Hot Lead Flyin'.
                <li>In the event of a tie in hand ranks, only the loser must discard/ace dudes (if it's a perfect tie,
                    i.e. two Dead Man's Hands, then there is no loser). (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114058#p1474905">Source</a>)
                <li>Casualties still apply, and the winner still has to cover as many as they can (matters if they have
                    Harrowed dudes or Sidekicks. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114735#p1483709">Source</a>)
                <li>A player can ace opposing dudes if he owns them (i.e. affected by Puppet). (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114582#p1481895">Source</a>)
                <li>Dude cards can still be discarded/aced from a player's hand (i.e. by This'll Hurt In The Mornin'). (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114829#p1484521">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="rope&ride"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "06019" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                  data-index="06019">Rope
                    and Ride</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Opposing a job is not the same as accepting a callout. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114833#p1484540">Source</a>)
                <li>You can use two of these in succession, if your dude has an unbooted horse. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114310#p1478471">Source</a>)
                <li>If you call out a dude at an opponent's private location, then move them to a public location, your
                    dudes will not get any bounty for breakin' and enterin'. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=113860#p1471988">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="incubation"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "06020" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                   data-index="06020">Incubation</a>
            </h4>
            <ul>
                <li>The affected dude's controller cannot use the ability printed on this card to reattach it to another
                    dude. (<a href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=113784#p1471119">Source</a>)
                <li>Forget cannot be used to remove the ability to discard Incubation from a dude. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114169#p1476548">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="flight"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "06021" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                               data-index="06021">Flight of
                    the Lepus</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>You can choose your dudes and opposing dudes at the same time. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=113761#p1470083">Source</a>)
                <li>You must boot either all of them or none. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114398#p1479644">Source</a>)
                <li>If you choose Tyxarglenak, you may also choose any hucksters in the opposing posse. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=113938#p1475274">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h2 id="sb05">No Turning Back</h2>
            <br>

            <h4 id="ebenezer"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "07003" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                 data-index="07003">Ebenezer
                    Springfield</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>'Affects' means 'Has a direct effect on your dude. Including boot/discard/ace your dude, turn him
                    from stud to draw, increase/decrease bullets/influence/value. Does not include an indirect effect
                    such as discarding an attached goods even if the loss of the goods affects the dude.' (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114278#p1478300">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="elanderxp"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "07004" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                  data-index="07004">Elander
                    Boldman (Exp.1)</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>If he is in a shootout, his ability cannot be used to unboot a Gadget outside of the shootout. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=113994#p1478316">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="antheia"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "07005" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                data-index="07005">Antheia
                    Pansofia</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>If Slade Lighbody pulls a club, then uses his ability and pulls another club, Antheia's bonus will
                    apply twice. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114309#p1478448">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="harry"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "07006" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                              data-index="07006">Harry
                    Highbinder</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Controlling the town square means you can attach goods to your dudes there by Shoppin' or Tradin',
                    attach Totems to the town square itself (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114723#p1483507">Source</a>), and
                    also use Stagecoach Office to bring in new dudes there.
            </ul>

            <h4 id="isham"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "07009" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                              data-index="07009">Jacqueline
                    Isham</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Don't forget to announce that you're using her ability, it doesn't trigger automatically.
                <li>Her ability can be used if any of your dudes (including herself) accepted a callout or opposed a
                    job. (<a href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114579#p1481950">Source</a>)
                <li>She remains a stud until the end of shootout. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114204#p1476946">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="asyncoil"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "07013" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                 data-index="07013">Asyncoil
                    Gun</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>The equipped dude makes the pull, not the player, so Doyle's Hoyle can be used. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114151#p1476298">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="scoop"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "07014" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                              data-index="07014">Scoop
                    Hound</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Prevents Shootout plays that bring new dudes into play and move them into a posse (Raising Hell,
                    Clown Carriage, Hired Help, Shane & Graves Security, Spirit Dance, The Pack Awakens). (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=113984#p1474030">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="tonic"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "07016" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                              data-index="07016">Vitality
                    Tonic</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>If the React ability is used, effects that trigger on a dude being aced (The Brute, The Undertaker)
                    do not trigger. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114281#p1478286">Source</a>)
                <li>If a dude is supposed to be aced to cover casualties but is saved with the Tonic's ability, that
                    dude is now considered as being discarded as a casualty, and thus can be further saved by Arnold
                    McCadish. (<a href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114322#p1478579">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="ntb"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "07021" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                            data-index="07021">No Turning
                    Back</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Token dudes can be aced normally. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114386#p1479472">Source</a>)
                <li>Acing a dude is part of the cost ("do X to do Y" format), thus React abilities cannot be used to
                    save that dude from being aced (Dr. Emanuel Ashbel, Vitality Tonic, Lay On Hands), but a Harrewed
                    dude will get discarded, not aced. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114454#p1480433">Source</a>)
                <li>Will set casualties to zero after Takin' Ya With Me and Hot Lead Flyin' increase them, effectively
                    negating these cards. (<a href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114734#p1483705">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h2 id="sb06">Nightmare at Noon</h2>
            <br>

            <h4 id="nathan"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "08004" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                               data-index="08004">Nathan
                    Shane</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Nathan's ability cannot be used if his bullet value is higher than the number of cards in your
                    opponent's hand. (<a href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&amp;t=115497"
                                         target="_blank">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="warren"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "08005" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                               data-index="08005">Warren
                    Graves</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Warren's ability can be used even if the only dude in a posse is about to get discarded / aced /
                    sent home, and the shootout will not end immediately. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114814#p1484371">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="radcliffe"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "08007" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                  data-index="08007">John
                    &quot;Aces&quot; Radcliffe</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>The effect of John's trait lasts until the end of the shootout. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114813#p1487984">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="duster"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "08013" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                               data-index="08013">Dog&#039;s
                    Duster</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Only prevents non-wanted Deputies from gaining a bounty for participating in a shootout at your
                    opponent's private location (breakin' and enterin'). Does not affect dudes who are already wanted,
                    and dudes participating in a Kidnappin'.
                </li>
                <li>The dude issuing a callout doesn't have to be the same dude that's wearing the Duster. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&amp;t=115511"
                            target="_blank">Source</a>)
            </ul>

            <h4 id="fsatat"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "08017" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                               data-index="08017">For Such a
                    Time as This</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>'This Miracle's skill check' means pull + modifiers, not difficulty.</li>
                <li>This card is aced only if the job succeeds and the spell is still in play. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=115076#p1487985">Source</a>)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h4 id="treasure"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "08020" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                 data-index="08020">Buried
                    Treasure</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Acing a dude card from the discard pile triggers the Undertaker.</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 id="n@n"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "08021" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                            data-index="08021">Nightmare at
                    Noon</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Only one Headline action can be played per shootout, for both players.</li>
                <li>Bullets are checked only once, when this card is played. Reducing bullets after that will not turn
                    stud dudes into draws. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&amp;t=115226#p1488912"
                            target="_blank">Source</a>)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="fp01">Immovable Object, Unstoppable Force</h2>
            <br>

            <h4 id="ben"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "09003" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                            data-index="09003">Benjamin
                    Washington</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>If you discard several cards, you may choose several dudes and give -2 upkeep to each one. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114730#p1483612">Source</a>)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h4 id="randall"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "09005" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                data-index="09005">Randall</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>At the start of the game you draw exactly 5 cards, not up to your maximum hand size. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114729#p1483609">Source</a>)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h4 id="hamshanks"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "09010" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                  data-index="09010">Hamshanks</a>
            </h4>
            <ul>
                <li>If Hamshanks is unbooted in a location you control and is equipped with a Mayfair Family Deck while
                    Tyxarglenak is also present, their protection effects cancel each other. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=115146#p1487982">Source</a>)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h4 id="sarah"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "09025" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                              data-index="09025">Sarah
                    Meoquanee</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Her trait references the Spirit keyword that spells have, not Spirit tokens. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114682#p1483180">Source</a>)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h4 id="crow"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "09027" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                             data-index="09027">Laughing
                    Crow</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>You can attach revealed Spirit spells to any of your Shamans anywhere, including booted and in
                    locations you don't control. This does not apply to Totems. (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114780#p1484044">Source</a>)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h4 id="nunchucks"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "09029" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                  data-index="09029">Nunchucks</a>
            </h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Can be used to affect pulls performed by the opponent or opposing dudes (skill checks, etc.) (<a
                            href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114844#p1484606">Source</a>)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h4 id="whatever"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "09030" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                 data-index="09030">Idol of
                    Tlazolteotl</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>To attach something legally means to attach it to something it could legally attach to as it enters
                    play. (<a href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114963#p1485907">Source</a>) That
                    also means you can only re-attch Totems to locations that you control where you have an unbooted
                    Shaman. (<a href="http://www.alderac.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=375&t=114966#p1485927">Source</a>)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h4 id="spirittrail"><a href="{{ path('cards_zoom', { card_code: "09033" }) }}" class="card card-title"
                                    data-index="09033">Spirit
                    Trail</a></h4>
            <ul>
                <li>If one Spirit Trail is attached to your home and another one to any deed (even out of town), your
